div.div:
Unable to hear, speak, or wield a sword, Prince Bojji doesn’t seem like a typical heir to the throne—and his kingdom agrees. But his fateful encounter with Kage, a shadow on the ground, gives him his first true friend. The two set off on a grand adventure and, together, form a bond that can overcome any obstacle...even being king.
(Source: Funimation)
Mushoku Tensei: Isekai Ittara Honki Dasu Part 2

Rudeus, Eris, and Rujierd head for Asura Kingdom in search of answers. Meanwhile, Roxy sets out across the Demon Continent to find Rudeus.
(Source: Funimation, edited)

Meet the would-be assassins of class 3-E: Sugino, who let his grades slip and got kicked off the baseball team. Karma, who’s doing well in his classes but keeps getting suspended for fighting. And Okuda, who lacks both academic and social skills, yet excels at one subject: chemistry. Who has the best chance of winning that reward? Will the deed be accomplished through pity, brute force or poison...? And what chance does their teacher have of repairing his students’ tattered self-esteem? (Source: Viz Media) Included Extra Chapters: Volume 1: Koro Sensei's Drawing Song Volume 2: Koro Sensei vs. Kusuo Saiki, Iruma City Battle Volume 7: Koro Sensei vs. Kusuo Saiki, Iruma City Battle II Volume 21: Time to Come Home Volume 21: Time to go to the Izakaya Volume 21: Time to Reveal Identities Volume 21: Time to Say Thank You Volume 21: Tokyo Department Store War Journal

Emma, Norman and Ray are the brightest kids at the Grace Field House orphanage. And under the care of the woman they refer to as “Mom,” all the kids have enjoyed a comfortable life. Good food, clean clothes and the perfect environment to learn—what more could an orphan ask for? One day, though, Emma and Norman uncover the dark truth of the outside world they are forbidden from seeing. (Source: Viz Media) Note: Nominated to the 22nd, 23rd, and 25th Annual Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize.
